Optional: Configure the Script to Start on Boot
If you want the script to start automatically on boot:

crontab -e

Add the following line to start the script after login:

@reboot /path/to/your/memory_monitor.sh

Replace /path/to/your/memory_monitor.sh with the actual path to the script. This setup will help keep you alerted if available memory drops or swap usage increases, helping you manage your system's resources effectively.

